# AhaDiff

Use AhaDiff to turn AI-written diffs into verified lessons, claims, quiz cards,
review signals, and local run artifacts.

- Run `ahadiff learn HEAD~1..HEAD` after committed changes.
- Run `ahadiff learn --staged` before committing staged work.
- Run `ahadiff quiz <run_id>` and `ahadiff review` to revisit generated cards.
- Use `ahadiff verify <run_id>` before trusting generated explanations.
- Use `ahadiff improve --rounds 1` when the diff needs a targeted follow-up.
- Open `ahadiff serve` for the local WebUI when inspecting run artifacts.

Additional learn capture modes: `ahadiff learn --last`, `ahadiff learn --since
"2 hours ago"`, `ahadiff learn --unstaged`, and `ahadiff learn --patch FILE|-`.

## Boundaries

- Keep provider credentials in environment variables.
- Do not commit `.ahadiff/audit.private.jsonl`.
- Treat `.ahadiff/` as local state.
- Prefer verified claims with file-line evidence.
- Do not upload `.ahadiff/` artifacts to external services without explicit user consent.
